Execution Strategy
Project Overview

The Intent Preservation Platform will be developed through a phased approach that builds on the completed benchmark, documented methodology, and interactive platform prototype. Rather than attempting to build a complete software platform at once, development will focus on creating a functional research MVP that can be iteratively improved through testing, mentorship, and community feedback.

Phase 1 — Research Foundation 

Status: Completed

Completed work includes:

Initial 20-case benchmark
Evaluation rubric
Failure categories
Research methodology
Initial findings
Interactive Figma prototype
GitHub documentation

This phase established the research foundation and demonstrated that intent preservation can be evaluated systematically.

Phase 2 — MVP Development

Status: Planned

The next phase focuses on transforming the research into a functional software platform.

Goals include:

Build the MVP from the Figma prototype.
Implement the benchmark workflow.
Integrate the evaluation rubric.
Enable structured benchmark reviews.
Generate standardized evaluation reports.

Development will be completed with a freelance software developer while I lead the research, product design, benchmark development, and project direction.

Phase 3 — Benchmark Expansion

Following MVP development, I will expand the benchmark by:

Developing additional benchmark cases.
Refining the evaluation methodology.
Improving the classification of AI failure patterns.
Testing multiple frontier language models.
Strengthening benchmark documentation.

The objective is to improve both the reliability and generalizability of the benchmark.

Phase 4 — Validation & Community Feedback

Once the MVP is functional, the platform will be shared with mentors, researchers, and early collaborators.

Feedback will be used to:

Improve usability.
Refine evaluation workflows.
Validate benchmark methodology.
Prioritize future platform development.

This stage is intended to ensure that the platform evolves in response to practical research needs.

Phase 5 — Open-Source Growth

The long-term goal is to establish the Intent Preservation Platform as an open-source research resource.

Future development will focus on:

Expanding benchmark domains beyond healthcare.
Improving automation.
Supporting additional language models.
Encouraging community contributions.
Building a sustainable evaluation framework that researchers can continue extending over time.
Current Execution Needs

The project's primary needs are:

Funding for MVP development.
Technical implementation support.
Continued mentorship.
Benchmark expansion.
API and cloud infrastructure.

The research foundation has already been established. The next stage is translating that work into a functional platform that researchers can actively use and improve.
